commit_message:
Use nova network-create --bridge for FlatDHCP

Although it's not documented anywhere, the --bridge-interface option is
only used by the VLAN network manager, but this page explicitly
uses FlatDHCP, so the --bridge option is appropriate.

Change-Id: I2bb13ba53cdc09171f16862f6915687a07de2150

commit_message:
cfn-signal provides a unique default id

Unless the parameter is provided, cfn-signal will use the instance UUID
from the Nova metadata as the id sent back to the WaitCondition.
In case the Nova metadata isn't available, it will use the hostname as a
fallback.

Change-Id: I1e5847c7babd7c6295d8c3e21f6cfa110a9b3026
Closes-bug: 1223429

For the ability to load same driver with different configurations
as different service providers, a service provider name is passed
to a driver when instantiated. Now, a driver can load it's configuration
according to the provider name received.
Driver path must not be unique anymore. Service type and provider name

Closes-Bug: #1264111
"}]
commit_message:
Multiple service providers with same driver

For the ability to load same driver with different configurations
as different service providers, a service provider name is passed
to a driver when instantiated. Now, a driver can load it's configuration
according to the provider name received.
Driver path must not be unique anymore. Service type and provider name
still should be a unique combination.
Driver configuration name in configuration file is not hardcoded
in code anymore.

Provider configuration and service type tests modified
according to new behavior.

Since driver can be used now with different provider name,
changed the logger name of radware driver to have the provider name.

Added specific unit test for testing the new capability

Change-Id: I01f28cb7e98edc2e1e288be69782726c17c2d196
Closes-Bug: #1264111

commit_message:
Add V2 nova client for PCI device info

All PCI pass through code is merged into nova, but the client does not
support it. This patch extends the API to show PCI information for
instance and compute node, and also provides a resource: endpoint to
show PCI infomation.

Partially implement blueprint pci-api-support

Change-Id: I5c1139a9ae8b9c51158b4f901c39a3c79b0b30c3

commit_message:
Enable create user without password

Keystone V2 ReST API allows create user without password, however,
CLI doesn't, this is because CLI will fill password with value None
while keystone server side doesn't accept such value.

This patch delete password field if it is not set.

Change-Id: I8542f99263ecd490212f91c1757b0aa7ee0bb624
Closes-Bug: #1273988

subject: Preserving older storage policies
revisions:
[{'number': 13, 'created': '2013-11-08 19:54:11.000000000', 'files': ['test/probe/test_container_failures.py', 'swift/common/db.py', 'swift/container/server.py', 'swift/container/replicator_rpc.py', 'swift/common/db_replicator.py', 'test/unit/common/test_db.py', 'swift/container/backend.py', 'test/unit/container/test_replicator_rpc.py'], 'message': 'Preserving older storage policies

The intention of this change is to preserve older storage
policy index metadata during container replication. This is
accomblished by modifying the method update_metadata of the
database broker and the creation of a ContainerReplicatorRpc
class.

The field "keep_older_meta" has been added to the database
broker and is empty by default. The subclass ContainerBroker
adds the storage policy index key to keep_older_meta. Update_metadata
only allows updates to keys inside of keep_older_meta when timestamps
are older or the same but the new value is greater. Unfortunately,
not having a storage policy index has meaning. We have to guard
against adding key/value pairs for keys in keep_older_meta to
existing containers that do not have those keys. We still need to
consider older containers without keys replicating with containers
with those keys.  Metadata alone is not enough.

The ContainerReplicatorRpc class fulfills the second part. It houses
the method "pre_sync" which can be optionally called from the parent
class's original sync method. This removes the double request for
replication_info in the previous iterations of this change.
pre_sync() identifies policy differences providing a starting point
to move objects and handles the case where on older container without
a policy is replicating with a newer container with a policy.

This change assumes that guarding metadata keys in keep_older_meta
from updates when the keys are not already in the metadata is the
general case.  If it is not the general case, we can move what would
then be storage policy index only logic into pre_sync and "prepare"
the metadata before it gets to update_metadata.

Change-Id: Icdc3b12814a28f5ee408e841a28b0d9728c79a37
'}]
commit_message:
Preserving older storage policies

The intention of this change is to preserve older storage
policy index metadata during container replication. This is
accomblished by modifying the method update_metadata of the
database broker and the creation of a ContainerReplicatorRpc
class.

The field "keep_older_meta" has been added to the database
broker and is empty by default. The subclass ContainerBroker
adds the storage policy index key to keep_older_meta. Update_metadata
only allows updates to keys inside of keep_older_meta when timestamps
are older or the same but the new value is greater. Unfortunately,
not having a storage policy index has meaning. We have to guard
against adding key/value pairs for keys in keep_older_meta to
existing containers that do not have those keys. We still need to
consider older containers without keys replicating with containers
with those keys.  Metadata alone is not enough.

The ContainerReplicatorRpc class fulfills the second part. It houses
the method "pre_sync" which can be optionally called from the parent
class's original sync method. This removes the double request for
replication_info in the previous iterations of this change.
pre_sync() identifies policy differences providing a starting point
to move objects and handles the case where on older container without
a policy is replicating with a newer container with a policy.

This change assumes that guarding metadata keys in keep_older_meta
from updates when the keys are not already in the metadata is the
general case.  If it is not the general case, we can move what would
then be storage policy index only logic into pre_sync and "prepare"
the metadata before it gets to update_metadata.

Change-Id: Icdc3b12814a28f5ee408e841a28b0d9728c79a37

commit_message:
Add parameter and iptables rules to protect dnsmasq ports

Add a paramater to the configuration file of the dhcp
agent. With this new param set as true, iptables rules
are inserted to limit dns requests to dnsmasq only to
the clients which are on the same subnet.

Change-Id: Iac3635326cb81d5de51b903510ff31cb6164aa86
Closes-bug: #1260731

commit_message:
Sync db.sqlalchemy module from Oslo

Now that the fix for bug 1231657 has been integrated into
Oslo-incubator, I need to sync the db.sqlalchemy module
to bring the change over to Cinder.  This sync includes
the following commits:

Change 12bcdb71: Remove vim header

commit_message:
Migrate oslo.messaging options to [oslo_messaging] config group

To help isolate configuration options from the main (application)
configuration opts registered, migrate the oslo.messaging specific
options to their own configuration group. All options have had
an explicit Deprecated option programatically added for the original
location in [DEFAULT] option group.

Change-Id: If80e6c7e1812765552fb4b27a028e7f0b6e242e0

commit_message:
REST deployment metadata method

A GET on the path /software_deployments/metadata/<server_id>
will return a list of software configs which should be deployed
to that server.

See the previous commit for the justification for this method.

In the future servers will be able to poll for this directly so
the policy.json does not have the deny_stack_user rule. Now that
this method exists software_deployments:index can now enforce
deny_stack_user.

partial blueprint hot-software-config-rest

Change-Id: I514677850cfb742bec85a5db75c71e6b2c7c9ea2

subject: RPC method to fetch deployments metadata
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-02-27 05:58:38.000000000', 'files': ['heat/tests/test_engine_service.py', 'heat/rpc/client.py', 'heat/engine/api.py', 'heat/rpc/api.py', 'heat/engine/service.py', 'heat/tests/test_engine_api_utils.py'], 'message': "RPC method to fetch deployments metadata

This method returns a list of software configs which are currently
deployed to a given server. Each config has the deployment input values
and current action inserted into it. This means that each config is
ephemeral and derived from the canonical config specified in the deployment
resource. The list of configs is sorted by config name. This allows the
template to control what order the configs are returned by setting the
'name' attribute of each deployment resource.

Having a separate RPC (and REST) method for deployment metadata also means
that servers will eventually be able to poll for deployment metadata directly,
avoiding the need to parse the stack for every poll.

partial blueprint hot-software-config-rest

Change-Id: I374f1e15d5255a3ad1264859fd845265cc60f218
"}]
commit_message:
RPC method to fetch deployments metadata

This method returns a list of software configs which are currently
deployed to a given server. Each config has the deployment input values
and current action inserted into it. This means that each config is
ephemeral and derived from the canonical config specified in the deployment
resource. The list of configs is sorted by config name. This allows the
template to control what order the configs are returned by setting the
'name' attribute of each deployment resource.

Having a separate RPC (and REST) method for deployment metadata also means
that servers will eventually be able to poll for deployment metadata directly,
avoiding the need to parse the stack for every poll.

partial blueprint hot-software-config-rest

Change-Id: I374f1e15d5255a3ad1264859fd845265cc60f218

commit_message:
Remove broken quota-classes API

It turns out os-quota-classes-sets never worked
(http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2014-February/027574.html). Since this doesn't work no need to keep it around.

V3 removal: Id1f288baa723df825151bd84aa27089271c2b8e4
Original commit: I6b6477481187d16af225d33c1989430e4071d5a8

This patch just removes the API it doesn't remove the quota-class
internals, that will be done in a subsequent patch.

Change-Id: I1110022d6f628d03aaf363da707f2d2ef1600437

commit_message:
Fix ceilometer parse invalid year num timestamp

iso8601 should raise reasonable error when parsing timestamp with invalid
years. this is implemented in iso8601 version 0.1.9.
More details please see the bug description and the issue on bitbucket.

Change-Id: Ied7d1878b26b2edaf37a9b5fc0b468ebfa2cb0e7
Closes-Bug: #1266398

On CentOS / Ubuntu, lbaas agent fails to start as we drop in a config

problematic as it doesn't have a default interface_driver set which

commit_message:
Point to correct lbaas_agent.ini file

On CentOS / Ubuntu, lbaas agent fails to start as we drop in a config
in a non-standard location.  The stock distro-provided config is also
problematic as it doesn't have a default interface_driver set which
prevents the service from starting.

This change defaults all distros to use /etc/neutron/lbaas_agent.ini
and tidies up ownership/mode of the dropped file.

Change-Id: I919e535989c5ec05ee196235fbd528eb971cbb05
Closes-Bug: #1283237

Multiple delete_port operations can run in parallel.

commit_message:
Handle racing condition in OFC port deletion

Multiple delete_port operations can run in parallel.
For such case later operation(s) will receive 404 (NotFound)
error from OFC or NotResultFound sqlalchemy exception.
These are valid exceptions and they should be ignored
in delete_port operations.

Closes-Bug: #1281574

OFCConsistencyBroken is renamed to OFCMappingNotFound
because when multiple delete_port operations run in parallel
OFCConsistencyBroken can occur and it is a valid case
so the excepion name looks inappropriate.

Change-Id: I1511d55994c88b8828f0ff62610c18ddc6dfac8f

commit_message:
TSM backup driver changes to support file backup

Extend TSM backup driver to support backup of file based volumes,
as well as restore and delete of the backups.  This in addition
to the current block based volume support.  This involves determining
the type of volume this is requested to be backed up, and modifying
the dsmc command options accordingly.  When a volume is backed
up, the backup mode and backup path are saved in the backup
service_metadata for use on restore and delete operations.

This commit includes some further refactoring based on pylint
feedback and system testing.

Implements: blueprint tsm-backup-driver-enhancement
Change-Id: Ic994a8c2f7302e59358dd858b50df746c9a7d76f

commit_message:
Add optional ionice to volume clearing process

Allow the volume clearing process to have an ionice priority set to
reduce the performance impact of volume zeroing. Note that this may
cause volume clearing processes to get backed up on  a busy system, use
with care.

DocImpact
Change-Id: I2d556f57aaca8a8ccc6f0f767f1cec28c3f9bc86
Implements: blueprint when-deleting-volume-dd-performance

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-27 02:36:40.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/scheduler/host_manager.py'], 'message': "Don't clear host_state_map when scheduling

host_state_map was added to scheduler for the purpose of caching latest
host_state in memory for scheduler.  With this cache, scheduler has the
latest host_state (e.g. free_capacity, allocated_capacity, etc) of hosts
even hosts haven't reported their updated status to scheduler.

Unfortunately, this cache is flushed when scheduling pulling all available
volume services from DB in current implementation, which is a bug.

This change remove the host_state_map.clear() so that scheduler is able to
maintain an up-to-date (well, mostly) view of all volume services in memory.
Also, added code to remove non-active host from the cache every time when
scheduler handles a new request.  Multi-line docstrings in cinder/scheduler/
host_manager.py are also fixed.

Change-Id: Ib47be483fa26631a1483721e2ae6d972994e150f
Fixes-bug: 1271162
"}]
commit_message:
Don't clear host_state_map when scheduling

host_state_map was added to scheduler for the purpose of caching latest
host_state in memory for scheduler.  With this cache, scheduler has the
latest host_state (e.g. free_capacity, allocated_capacity, etc) of hosts
even hosts haven't reported their updated status to scheduler.

Unfortunately, this cache is flushed when scheduling pulling all available
volume services from DB in current implementation, which is a bug.

This change remove the host_state_map.clear() so that scheduler is able to
maintain an up-to-date (well, mostly) view of all volume services in memory.
Also, added code to remove non-active host from the cache every time when
scheduler handles a new request.  Multi-line docstrings in cinder/scheduler/
host_manager.py are also fixed.

Change-Id: Ib47be483fa26631a1483721e2ae6d972994e150f
Fixes-bug: 1271162

subject: Improve local-config proxy handling.
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-02-27 11:02:54.000000000', 'files': ['elements/local-config/pre-install.d/02-proxy-settings'], 'message': "Improve local-config proxy handling.

We were applying proxy settings after apt-get install runs are done
in the Ubuntu element, which made it ineffective. Secondly, we were
not applying no_proxy settings to apt, which caused it to fail in
corporate settings. More explicit control may be facilitated in future
but local-config is a DTRT tool, and so we should help it DTRT.

I think I've correctly setup Zypper for this, and I have no idea
how to make the same improvement for Yum (and also Yum currently
doesn't set HTTPS proxies, which may lead to similar reports there).

Change-Id: Idbb9781d64d44b717ea22a25429383fa45d84148
"}]
commit_message:
Improve local-config proxy handling.

We were applying proxy settings after apt-get install runs are done
in the Ubuntu element, which made it ineffective. Secondly, we were
not applying no_proxy settings to apt, which caused it to fail in
corporate settings. More explicit control may be facilitated in future
but local-config is a DTRT tool, and so we should help it DTRT.

I think I've correctly setup Zypper for this, and I have no idea
how to make the same improvement for Yum (and also Yum currently
doesn't set HTTPS proxies, which may lead to similar reports there).

Change-Id: Idbb9781d64d44b717ea22a25429383fa45d84148

commit_message:
Add support for tenant_id based authentication with Neutron

Keystone v3 supports non-unique project/tenant names, so
Nova should switch to using tenant ID for admin authentication.

Implements blueprint tenant-id-based-auth-for-neutron
DocImpact: Adds new flag, nova_admin_tenant_id, and deprecates
existing flag, nova_admin_tenant_name

Change-Id: I4a4ffe84fdcf98ace81fd148f096cad483aad96c

commit_message:
Export and import backup service metadata

Add new admin API for backup-export and backup-import.
The new commands export the backup details (not actual backup) to
a string that can be imported again in another OpenStack cloud or
if the backup database was corrupted.
The code includes a default backup driver implementation.
Backup test code converted to use mock.

blueprint cinder-backup-recover-api
DocImpact new admin API calls backup-import and backup-export

Change-Id: I564194929962e75c67630e73d8711ee6587706d4

commit_message:
NSX: Pass NSX uuid when plugging l2 gw attachment

The code passed the neutron network identifier.
This is no longer valid as identifiers on the backend are not
anymore the same as neutron identifiers.

Also, this would have hardly worked with networks on extended
logical switches.

Closes-Bug: 1285399

subject: Make admin_bind_host configurable
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-24 18:43:44.000000000', 'files': ['lib/keystone'], 'message': 'Make admin_bind_host configurable

The use case is running devstack inside an OpenStack vm and running tempest
from some other machine. To make the catalog export urls that can be accessed
from off the devstack machine, you need to set KEYSTONE_SERVICE_HOST to an
external IP. But devstack uses that address in its setup of keystone in
addition to exporting in the catalog. Because OpenStack has an issue where
a vm cannot access itself through its own floating ip, devstack fails. There
is no way to have this use case by providing an ip address. The workaround
is to use the hostname of the devstack machine. That worked until recently
when a change was made to set admin_bind_host to the value of
KEYSTONE_SERVICE_HOST. The result is that port 35357 is only opened locally.
This change allows the devstack user to restore the original behavior
allowing this use case.

Change-Id: I97b938b305b7dd878397e7e64462650064e59cd2
Closes-Bug: #1283803
'}]
commit_message:
Make admin_bind_host configurable

The use case is running devstack inside an OpenStack vm and running tempest
from some other machine. To make the catalog export urls that can be accessed
from off the devstack machine, you need to set KEYSTONE_SERVICE_HOST to an
external IP. But devstack uses that address in its setup of keystone in
addition to exporting in the catalog. Because OpenStack has an issue where
a vm cannot access itself through its own floating ip, devstack fails. There
is no way to have this use case by providing an ip address. The workaround
is to use the hostname of the devstack machine. That worked until recently
when a change was made to set admin_bind_host to the value of
KEYSTONE_SERVICE_HOST. The result is that port 35357 is only opened locally.
This change allows the devstack user to restore the original behavior
allowing this use case.

Change-Id: I97b938b305b7dd878397e7e64462650064e59cd2
Closes-Bug: #1283803

commit_message:
Remove db query from deallocate_fixed_ip

A previous patch updated deallocate_for_instance() in nova-network to
take the full instance object over rpc.  This patch passes that instance
through nova-network to deallocate_fixed_ip(), which allows us to avoid
N instance db lookups (where N is the number of fixed IPs being
deallocated).

Related to blueprint nova-network-objects

Change-Id: Ib92e824f1bea2caae668945fabfae997632cd5f0

subject: Savanna: use heat infra engine if available
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-25 09:30:23.000000000', 'files': ['lib/savanna'], 'message': 'Savanna: use heat infra engine if available

In Savanna we have two provisioning engines:

* "savanna" that directly work with nova/neutron/glance/cinder/etc and
   we'd like to deprecate it early in Juno release cycle, but it's still
   useful due to the fact that it could work ok w/o Heat;
* "heat" engine uses Heat for provisioning of cluster resources, it's
   currently under active development and we're ready to make it default
   for OpenStack installations with enabled Heat.

Change-Id: I937337b3921e9e51768a118fb4b6bd95962622bd
'}]
commit_message:
Savanna: use heat infra engine if available

In Savanna we have two provisioning engines:

* "savanna" that directly work with nova/neutron/glance/cinder/etc and
   we'd like to deprecate it early in Juno release cycle, but it's still
   useful due to the fact that it could work ok w/o Heat;
* "heat" engine uses Heat for provisioning of cluster resources, it's
   currently under active development and we're ready to make it default
   for OpenStack installations with enabled Heat.

Change-Id: I937337b3921e9e51768a118fb4b6bd95962622bd

commit_message:
Fix NSX migration path

The migration path for the NSX plugin was not working correctly,
as two migrations (extra route and network gateways) were
skipped.
Therefore installations were partially relying on automatic
schema generation.

This patch fixes the migration path, as well as an attribute
whose name in the migration and the DB model differed.

Closes-Bug: 1285095

Change-Id: I9e4db294e618d1419d86e07cfb5505dcc01b54ca

commit_message:
Enable flake8 with tox

Devstack has not only shell scripts but also python tools. So we should
check whether the code keep the hacking rules.

This commit just enables flake8 checking with tox. But it ignores most
of the rules for keeping patches small.

Change-Id: I56bd516e23eebedc4d3ad66fcc514bdca008e1c1

If pip_install fails it is sure that dependencies will be missing,
leading to (often) bizarre looking errors much later on.  Thus such a
failure should be fatal to the ongoing operation of devstack.

Change-Id: I0f4a2988e0601812ca373cc3bffc8c7dc3549695
'}]
commit_message:
Ensure pip_install failure is fatal

If pip_install fails it is sure that dependencies will be missing,
leading to (often) bizarre looking errors much later on.  Thus such a
failure should be fatal to the ongoing operation of devstack.

Change-Id: I0f4a2988e0601812ca373cc3bffc8c7dc3549695

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-12 19:04:23.000000000', 'files': ['horizon/test/tests/base.py'], 'message': 'get_user_home test fix for django 1.6

In django 1.6, the django.utils.html.strip_tags method no longer
calls force_text on the object passed in.  This causes a
get_user_home test to fail as it attempts to concatenate the User
object and a str and fails.  Changing to a method that will take
an Object.

Partially-implements: blueprint django-1point6
'}]
commit_message:
get_user_home test fix for django 1.6

In django 1.6, the django.utils.html.strip_tags method no longer
calls force_text on the object passed in.  This causes a
get_user_home test to fail as it attempts to concatenate the User
object and a str and fails.  Changing to a method that will take
an Object.

Change-Id: If879a1597fe334f67a3f7109defa0694db005f81
Partially-implements: blueprint django-1point6

commit_message:
Replace '+' with string interpolation operation

Replace string concatenation of translated messages with string
interpolation operation, since the gettextutils.Message object
doesn't support the '+' operation, which will cause problem when
lazy translation is enalbed.

Change-Id: I2c8a271ef766ab0da81b1c320870bbc429f6207e

commit_message:
Add a caching scheduler driver

This adds a new scheduler driver, CachingScheduler

It currently subclasses the filter scheduler and only adds caching of
calls to host_manager.get_all_host_states.

It relies on there being a small number of schedulers, ideally one,
calls to consume_from_instance within the filter scheduler to update the
current cached list of hosts, and a low rate of deletes.

It introduces the new config value:
scheduler_driver_task_period

The periodic task it controls is used by the caching scheduler to fetch
an updated copy of host_manager.get_all_host_states.

If your value for service_down_time is much smaller than
scheduler_driver_task_period, there will be issues with hosts appearing
to be dead, just because the list of hosts is being cached. Correct
configuration of those two values can avoid this issue.

DocImpact
Part of blueprint caching-scheduler
Change-Id: I2eb873ce8024a576e597205e2d52b5d5e8aee97a

commit_message:
Guard against oversize flavor rxtx_factor float

We now check that rxtx_factor provided is not greater than
the Float type to be stored in the db. While the check is not
100% accurate due to float approximation it will be very
close to the max allowable. A 400 error is returned if the
provided value is too big.

Closes-Bug: 1259213
Change-Id: I72c52fa46d75275c45e72b6f5a36106d5abf8220
Co-authored-by: Takashi Natsume <natsume.takashi@lab.ntt.co.jp>

commit_message:
enable -o errexit

devstack should run under -o errexit to ensure that we fail early
when something has gone wrong, otherwise determination of the root
failure location is often quite challenging.

this clears all the normal use cases for devstack, there could be
tests which now die early, which we're going to have to check for
later.

Change-Id: Ibd828c4f4fd95a60d3918d3d7ae90e10649479ab

commit_message:
Added HOT Template for 2 Servers Without Floating IPs

Previously, a HOT template existed for deploying 2 servers using
an existing Neutron network and assigning Floating IPs to provide
public access.  This template does not work well when using
Neutron Provider Networking Extensions where Floating IPs are
unneeded to directly access instances. The template also creates
and associates the 2 servers to a Neutron Security Group that
allows SSH and ICMP.

Change-Id: Id827ce8fe2ea705066ca536bfe86e5a06a3fce2a

commit_message:

subject: Fix regex for file size to parse float-style numbers properly
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-27 16:37:03.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/common/imageutils.py'], 'message': "Fix regex for file size to parse float-style numbers properly

The SIZE_RE regex was not accounting for the fact that the size of the
file can be reported as a float style number (eg '2.0G') and so the size
of the file was not being reported in bytes correctly.

Change-Id: Id584b7d6710245cf7787f557d1ec87b569d943f7
Closes-Bug: #1285764
"}]
commit_message:
Fix regex for file size to parse float-style numbers properly

The SIZE_RE regex was not accounting for the fact that the size of the
file can be reported as a float style number (eg '2.0G') and so the size
of the file was not being reported in bytes correctly.

Change-Id: Id584b7d6710245cf7787f557d1ec87b569d943f7
Closes-Bug: #1285764

[{'number': 19, 'created': '2014-02-26 13:35:33.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/common/db/options.py'], 'message': 'Make TRADITIONAL the default SQL mode

Rather than log a warning when TRADITIONAL mode is not enabled,
just make it the default. If this causes INSERTs or UPDATEs from

broken data to begin with.

Change-Id: I84c1781454ed5f46c7a135c96bafc575f313f9bc

commit_message:
Make TRADITIONAL the default SQL mode

Rather than log a warning when TRADITIONAL mode is not enabled,
just make it the default. If this causes INSERTs or UPDATEs from
applications to break, it just exposes that they are inserting
broken data to begin with.

Change-Id: I84c1781454ed5f46c7a135c96bafc575f313f9bc

commit_message:
neutron-metering-agent service name is wrong

In Ubuntu the neutron-metering-agent package and Upstart service are named
neutron-plugin-metering-agent. In Debian they are named
neutron-metering-agent.

Partial-Bug: #1284179
(cherry picked from commit 57e16648629b8c541e094b848cecac53137949c4)

Change-Id: I76b56886a4d239b279731dc1e85c17a7f380aa76

commit_message:
Remove oslo.uuidutils

The only use of uuidutils in barbican is generate_uuid
which will be dropped from oslo-incubator.

This patch moves generate_uuid to barbican.common.utils and
updates the context module from oslo.

Following changes were updated in context:

13eb01c Adding domain to context and log
12bcdb7 Remove vim header
bdabd51 Remove uuidutils imports in oslo modules
44e8222 Revert "Removes generate_uuid from uuidutils"
571a78a Removes generate_uuid from uuidutils
36859e5 Adding instance_uuid to context and log

Change-Id: If27f8308f00ce92d8cde0bc1c669c8020137eba5
Partial-bug: #1253497

commit_message:
Enable flake8 H404 checking

This check indicates on comments in which multi line docstring should
start without a leading new line. This change fixed all violators of
said check.

commit_message:
Skip test_get_instance_action test for nova v3

InstanceActionsV3Test.test_get_instance_action() relies on the
x-compute-request-id header existing in the response from create_test_server()
in setUpClass(). That header name is going to be replaced for nova v3,
pending change I5e370fd3de5ee2f8a8d13553015d88910ff5ea87

So for now, skip that test in v3. The header name can be updated after the nova
change merges.

Change-Id: Ia1880dd53b7cbf34e66b349f01afb15672dffd12

commit_message:
Don't store engine instances in oslo.db (WIP)

This patch is a quick-and-dirty proof of concept for remove engine
instances from oslo.db code. See patch in oslo-incubator -
I330467ec1317e1a13ff9f0237e2d8900d718e379

We don't want to store any engine instances globally in oslo.db and
suppose, that it's up to end applications to decide how to cope with
engines.

Change-Id: Icf4e33c963080c4b3b2f9e264f415348f77fadad

VPNaaS service name is wrong

In Ubuntu the VPNaaS service name and package are

are neutron-vpn-agent.

commit_message:
Update pre_live_migration to take instance object

Update the pre_live_migration method in the compute api, compute manager,
and virt driver to take an instance object.  The update to the compute manager
call also happens to finish the conversion of
ensure_filtering_rules_for_instance in the virt driver API, as well.

Part of blueprint virt-objects

commit_message:
Install lvm2 package for cinder

Adds lvm2 package to get installed for the cinder package install. lvm2
is needed by the 72-cinder-resize-volume-groups os-refresh-config script
since that script uses the "vgs" command.

commit_message:
Mildly wound the interlopers

This commit removes all the references to nose in the tempest tree.
Moving forward trying to support nose which doesn't support some of the
features we rely on in tempest is increasingly difficult. Please refer
to this thread:

http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2014-January/024673.html

for a more detailed explanation and the discussion regarding this.

Change-Id: I3dee566d33efe1fb7808817b885d1680736abe6a

subject: Fixes a race condition in resize flavor for Percona
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-26 06:12:46.000000000', 'files': ['trove/tests/api/instances_resize.py', 'trove/taskmanager/models.py'], 'message': 'Fixes a race condition in resize flavor for Percona

When a resize happens immediately after an instances gets created,
the mysql process doesnt have enough time to finished up
provisioning before the resize-action invokes a stop and start
resizing. Although the trove tries to stop mysql, the stop command
doesnt ensure that mysql was stopped successfully. This causes
mysql to be corrupted when migrated to a different VM. Normally
this is not an issue since mysql provisioning has plenty of time
to finish. This becomes an issue when doing an resize when mysql
has just finished provisioned. Only happens in automated tests.
This fix will ensure that the mysql server is stopped before a
resize is performed.

Change-Id: I0a3c351b61b82b88dfe05325a38ce93d6973a9f6
Closes-Bug: 1284989
'}]
commit_message:
Fixes a race condition in resize flavor for Percona

When a resize happens immediately after an instances gets created,
the mysql process doesnt have enough time to finished up
provisioning before the resize-action invokes a stop and start
resizing. Although the trove tries to stop mysql, the stop command
doesnt ensure that mysql was stopped successfully. This causes
mysql to be corrupted when migrated to a different VM. Normally
this is not an issue since mysql provisioning has plenty of time
to finish. This becomes an issue when doing an resize when mysql
has just finished provisioned. Only happens in automated tests.
This fix will ensure that the mysql server is stopped before a
resize is performed.

Change-Id: I0a3c351b61b82b88dfe05325a38ce93d6973a9f6
Closes-Bug: 1284989

commit_message:
Renaming plugin-specific exceptions to match NSX

Try to get rid of Nvp as much as possible, the base
class already uses the plugin short name so it's
pointless to carry it over.

Partial-implements blueprint nicira-plugin-renaming

reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 2472, 'name': 'Doug Hellmann', 'email': 'dhellmann@redhat.com', 'username': 'doug-hellmann'}, {'_account_id': 5638, 'name': 'Davanum Srinivas', 'email': 'davanum@gmail.com', 'username': 'dims-v'}, {'_account_id': 7491, 'name': 'Viktor Serhieiev', 'email': 'viktor.sergeyev@gmail.com', 'username': 'vsergeyev'}, {'_account_id': 7763, 'name': 'Alexei Kornienko', 'email': 'akornienko@mirantis.com', 'username': 'akornienko'}, {'_account_id': 8041, 'name': 'Petr Blaho', 'email': 'pblaho@redhat.com', 'username': 'pblaho'}, {'_account_id': 9550, 'name': 'Eugeniya Kudryashova', 'email': 'ekudryashova@mirantis.com', 'username': 'ekudryashova'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-01-30 15:05:43.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/common/apiclient/base.py', 'tests/unit/apiclient/test_base.py'], 'message': "Removed set_loaded() method from Resource class

set_loaded() method should not be available in class public API cause its
usage can break internal class logic. Base Resource class(method __getattr__)
can behave incorrectly if access to attribute _loaded is provided to end users.

method get() of Resource class also should be private, because it's
related to internal class logic and doesn't have any meaning from
outside of the class

blueprint common-client-library-2

Change-Id: I491f9b54c7074546cf738c6150666bfcc3966a78
"}]
commit_message:
Removed set_loaded() method from Resource class

set_loaded() method should not be available in class public API cause its
usage can break internal class logic. Base Resource class(method __getattr__)
can behave incorrectly if access to attribute _loaded is provided to end users.

method get() of Resource class also should be private, because it's
related to internal class logic and doesn't have any meaning from
outside of the class

blueprint common-client-library-2

Change-Id: I491f9b54c7074546cf738c6150666bfcc3966a78

'name' should as be optional param on aggregate-update

'name' should be an optional parameter not required on aggregate-update,
so we can update 'availability_zone' only.

Reasons:
- When provisioning a guest using heat code-path, the guest agent shows
  errors in first-boot.d.log, which is because first-boot tries to start
  trove-guest service before /etc/guest_info file is created by heat
  provisioning.

Changes:
- Adds condition to start trove-guest, to check existence of
  /etc/guest_info, if file exists, then start trove-guest.

Closes-Bug: #1278733
'}]
commit_message:
Starts trove-guest if /etc/trove exists

Reasons:
- When provisioning a guest using heat code-path, the guest agent shows
  errors in first-boot.d.log, which is because first-boot tries to start
  trove-guest service before /etc/guest_info file is created by heat
  provisioning.

Changes:
- Adds condition to start trove-guest, to check existence of
  /etc/guest_info, if file exists, then start trove-guest.

Change-Id: I112822fa69b2d4a49d29457fa4b1acf06206c52e
Closes-Bug: #1278733

commit_message:
update deallocate_for_instance to take instance obj

Update the deallocate_for_instance() method of the nova.network rpc API
to take a full instance object instead of just an instance UUID and some
other instance data.  This patch is just the mechanics of getting the
API changed.  The next patch will make use of getting the full instance
object to eliminate a db query in nova-network.

Part of blueprint nova-network-objects

Change-Id: I9be88206ecc64a92d2826a9ac43e4d2d384f29ff

in the db manage session. It gives an alarming message
so correctly setup the session with tradition mode on.

commit_message:
Remove dependency on log.py from openstack/common

Importing oslo.vmware to another OpenStack project gives the
ArgsAlreadyParsedError: arguments already parsed: cannot register CLI
option exception.
This happens because openstack/common/log.py registers CLI options
after the project using oslo.vmware parses its configuration.

This patch addresses this issue by removing any dependency on
log.py, using logging from the standard python library instead.

Change-Id: Id2bddb8a7efc2a53399e2a2278dba4605da083d8
Closes-Bug: #1284837

commit_message:
NetApp copy offload implementation for clustered nfs driver

Copy offload is a special RPC implemented in Ontap that
allows NFS clients to ask the server to copy data between
volumes in the same cluster efficiently. The special
binary will be developed by NetApp and distributed to its customers.
It will address two copy cases after efficient image clone failed.
First when image cache file is present in a different share than
the one holding volume. Second when glance is backed by nfs share
which is on the same cluster as nfs driver backend. Instead
of regular http download the copy offload workflow will be used to copy
image to share and volume.

Implements: blueprint copyoffload
Related-Bug: 1277005

Change-Id: Ib95f7b3890b55b6354f2b3b5e4458a99aee30e7d

commit_message:
Update server_diagnostics to use instance object

Update the server_diagnostics API to get an instance object and then pass it
through the system down to the virt driver.

Converting the get_diagnostics() call in the compute manager also updates one of
the driver.get_info() calls to take an instance object.  Most had already been
converted.  There was one other stray case in the compute manager where it was
still taking an instance primitive, so this patch hits that one too to finish
the conversion of get_info() while we're at it.

Part of blueprint virt-objects

Change-Id: I20b324039c20f5b1fde4d55df2d679b7fb094573

path is specified i.e.

    <backend model='random'/>
  </rng>

It's preferable for us to not duplicate this default to allow for a
future where libvirt or the hypervisor needs to make more intelligent
decisions about the default device to use.

Also, improve the unit tests to catch this issue.

Change-Id: Ia0f922f7de575496972b4dfa9d56aa22205f1758

commit_message:
libvirt: remove explicit /dev/random rng default

libvirt (or rather qemu) will default to /dev/random if no rng device
path is specified i.e.

  <rng model='virtio'>
    <backend model='random'/>
  </rng>

It's preferable for us to not duplicate this default to allow for a
future where libvirt or the hypervisor needs to make more intelligent
decisions about the default device to use.

Also, improve the unit tests to catch this issue.

Change-Id: Ia0f922f7de575496972b4dfa9d56aa22205f1758

commit_message:
LBaaS: apply loadbalancer instance for agent and haproxy driver

Handle lb instance as new root object in lbaas agent and haproxy driver.
Additianally this forms a base for applying l7 rules for haproxy.

NOTE: the change in the agent  RPC API is backward-incompatible
(major RPC version change), LBaaS server-agent communications will be
completely broken until both sides are upgraded. However this is the
second major lbaas agent API change during Icehouse so it should not
bring any additional problems during upgrade from Havana.

partially implements bp lbaas-service-instance

Change-Id: I8c860c51771587f3d62f208306dc18d62697c348

commit_message:
LBaaS: apply agent scheduling for loadbalancer instance

Since loadbalancer instance becomes the root object in LBaaS model
we need to bind instance to an agent instead of binding the pool

Existing pool related lbaas_agent_scheduler API operations are left
for backward compatibility

DocImpact:
pool related lbaas_agent_scheduler API operations should be marked
as deprecated:
List pools the given LBaaS agent is hosting:
 GET /agents/agent_id/loadbalancer-pools
Show a LBaaS agent hosting the given pool:
 GET /lb/pools/pool_id/loadbalancer-agent
New lbaas_agent_scheduler API operations:
List loadbalancers the given LBaaS agent is hosting:
 GET /agents/agent_id/loadbalancer-instances
Show an LBaaS agent hosting the given loadbalancer:
 GET /lb/loadbalancers/loadbalancer_id/loadbalancer-agent

partially implements bp lbaas-service-instance

Change-Id: If76b407510f90253e59d796a318c09163fa45acb

commit_message:
Allow services to be multiple-worker

Add the ability to run every nova service as multiple processes.

This will help scaling where C calls can block the eventlet hub from
switching greenthreads.  (Example: MySQLdb driver)

Processes are referred to as "workers" in the code.

Multiple *_workers config flags have been added to control the
number of workers.  These mimic the style of the existing flags used
by the API services.

The ProcessLauncher code is not Windows compatible (Windows pipes don't
support non-blocking I/O) so default to 1 worker.

DocImpact

Change-Id: If0d7f36e348d9a0b2e62094fcb8fdea612f3a843

commit_message:
VMware: Store vCenter passwords in keystone credential store

Gives the VMware driver the capability to lookup the vcenter user and

commit_message:
Fix race condition in network scheduling to dhcp agent

Rarely dhcp agent rpc call get_active_networks_info() can interleave
with network scheduling initiated by create.port.end notification.
In this case scheduling raises and port creation returns 500.
Need to synchronize on DhcpNetworkBindings table.

Closes-Bug: #1276552
Change-Id: I52d94a40772a99c7032dba15b200bf0f21362f93
(cherry picked from commit eed1b7cbdb00a3fbac9f19bab1a2d7366833b753)

commit_message:
DO NOT MERGE: Full oslo-incubator sync

Generated with:
'./update.sh --config-file ../cinder/openstack-common.conf --base cinder
--dest-dir ../cinder'

This patch is a test to see how many things break when doing this.

Following modules aren't require changes to cinder codebase, and are
skipped here:
* db
* policy
* strutils: backwards incompatible changes to strutils.to_string
* imageutils: depends on strutils
* lockutils: backwards incompatible change

Change-Id: Icd81b2519531e747d4e2dec88bc556cf371e2175

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-01-09 08:01:17.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/test_quota.py', 'nova/compute/api.py'], 'message': 'incorrectly quota check for injected_file_contents

File content to be injected as part of instance creation is constrained
by the injected_file_content_bytes quota. The file content need to be
encoded in the client and will be decoded in compute/manager.py. So,
the quota check in compute/api.py is performed against the encoded contents.
However the contents and the encoded contents are not equal in length.
So, it will fails when it should pass if the contents is very close to
the quota limit. We should decoded the contents when check quota.

Change-Id: I4b62665c785f294dd05a4c4ddb95aa107334d77a
Closes-Bug: #1225143
'}]
commit_message:
incorrectly quota check for injected_file_contents

File content to be injected as part of instance creation is constrained
by the injected_file_content_bytes quota. The file content need to be
encoded in the client and will be decoded in compute/manager.py. So,
the quota check in compute/api.py is performed against the encoded contents.
However the contents and the encoded contents are not equal in length.
So, it will fails when it should pass if the contents is very close to
the quota limit. We should decoded the contents when check quota.

Change-Id: I4b62665c785f294dd05a4c4ddb95aa107334d77a
Closes-Bug: #1225143

commit_message:
ValueError should use '%' instead of ','

The method _load_service_plugins() in /neutron/neutron/managers.py
throw a ValueError using ',' to connect log and variables.
ValueError do not support using ',' to connect log and variables,
we should use '%' instead.

Change-Id: I3567e1769e7e2bdfc6eb2e82c5cb2ee060c73829
Closes-Bug:#1264210

commit_message:
Prepare for enabling H302 rule (thirdparty)

We can use H302 rule but ignore it now. This commit prepares for
enabling H302 rule. But this commit modifies tempest/thirdparty only
and excludes some violations[1] because if we fix all of them at one
time, it's hard to merge this commit.

commit_message:
Catch HostBinaryNotFound exception when updating a service

When updating a service with a wrong host or binary name,
HostBinaryNotFound exception is raised. However this exception
isn't caught and the ServiceNotFound exception which won't happen
here is caught instead.
This patch fixes this bug.

Change-Id: I64b138bad74c39d087addcd766b890c4076a2ce8
Closes-Bug: #1273139

commit_message:
DB Mappings for NSX security groups

This patch introduces DB mappings between neutron security
groups and NSX security profiles, thus not requiring anymore
the Neutron router ID to be equal to the NSX one.

This change is needed for enabling asynchronous operations in
the NSX plugin.

Related to blueprint nvp-async-backend-communication

Change-Id: I3b28d535c93cd2bfc776aabe0d99be18fce4454d

subject: swift.1 manpage fix for groff warnings
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-18 03:49:39.000000000', 'files': ['doc/manpages/swift.1'], 'message': 'swift.1 manpage fix for groff warnings

The current manual page contains hyphens where a minus sign
was intended. By default, "-" chars are interpreted as
hyphens (U+2010) by groff, not as minus signs (U+002D).
Since options to programs use minus signs (U+002D), this
means for example in UTF-8 locales that you cannot cut and
paste options, nor search for them easily.

This patch fixes this by escaping hyphens with backslashes,
and also fixes a typo: s/retreived/retrieved/.

Change-Id: If954c91eebe7b39bdac792f1f126998d2e3bcb8e
'}]
commit_message:
swift.1 manpage fix for groff warnings

The current manual page contains hyphens where a minus sign
was intended. By default, "-" chars are interpreted as
hyphens (U+2010) by groff, not as minus signs (U+002D).
Since options to programs use minus signs (U+002D), this
means for example in UTF-8 locales that you cannot cut and
paste options, nor search for them easily.

This patch fixes this by escaping hyphens with backslashes,
and also fixes a typo: s/retreived/retrieved/.

Change-Id: If954c91eebe7b39bdac792f1f126998d2e3bcb8e

subject: Add HEAD api response for test s3 server BucketHandler
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-02-26 17:43:57.000000000', 'files': ['nova/objectstore/s3server.py', 'nova/tests/test_objectstore.py'], 'message': 'Add HEAD api response for test s3 server BucketHandler

Current nova test s3 server lacks HEAD for BucketHandler. And it becomes
an issue for Boto after version 2.25.0 [1], which changes underlying
implementation of get_bucket method from GET to HEAD request.

This change fixes this gap by adding HEAD response to test s3 server.
And also added cases for testing bucket existence per Boto document
suggestion[2], which applies for both Boto prior to or after version
2.25.0

[1] http://docs.pythonboto.org/en/latest/releasenotes/v2.25.0.html
[2] http://docs.pythonboto.org/en/latest/s3_tut.html#accessing-a-bucket

Closes-bug: #1277790
(cherry picked from commit 033f3776c4bc6d0db14b1b9da7c24e207e9628ab)
(cherry picked from commit 2abcc4e04c9838d1130ef18c0efd697cc8cc6918)

Change-Id: If992efa40f7f36d337d1b9b1f52859aa0ae51874
'}]
commit_message:
Add HEAD api response for test s3 server BucketHandler

Current nova test s3 server lacks HEAD for BucketHandler. And it becomes
an issue for Boto after version 2.25.0 [1], which changes underlying
implementation of get_bucket method from GET to HEAD request.

This change fixes this gap by adding HEAD response to test s3 server.
And also added cases for testing bucket existence per Boto document
suggestion[2], which applies for both Boto prior to or after version
2.25.0

[1] http://docs.pythonboto.org/en/latest/releasenotes/v2.25.0.html
[2] http://docs.pythonboto.org/en/latest/s3_tut.html#accessing-a-bucket

Closes-bug: #1277790
(cherry picked from commit 033f3776c4bc6d0db14b1b9da7c24e207e9628ab)
(cherry picked from commit 2abcc4e04c9838d1130ef18c0efd697cc8cc6918)

subject: Add end-of-file checks to bash8
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-02-25 22:33:31.000000000', 'files': ['lib/neutron_plugins/embrane', 'lib/nova_plugins/hypervisor-libvirt', 'tools/bash8.py'], 'message': 'Add end-of-file checks to bash8

Add two end-of-file checks to bash8.  Firstly, alert if heredoc hasn't
finished.  Some heredocs were done like:

---
sudo bash -c "cat <<EOF > foo
...
EOF"
---

(A better way to do this is "cat <<EOF | sudo tee ..." as it retains
the usual heredoc layout in the code).

The trailing quote was throwing the matching in bash8 off and it kept
appending the next file as if it was still part of the heredoc.  To
avoid this, we check if we're still in a heredoc when we start a new
file; if so raise an error and reset the heredoc status fresh.  We
track the state of the previous file, line and lineno so we can give a
good error.

---
E012: heredoc did not end before EOF: 'cat <<EOF'
 - lib/trove: L221
---

This includes fixes for the existing problem heredocs.

A similar EOF check is to ensure the previous file ended with a
newline.

---
E004: file did not end with a newline: '$MY_XTRACE'
 - lib/neutron_plugins/embrane: L40
---

This requires only one fix

Change-Id: I5e547d87b3921fc7ce6588c28f074e5c9f489c1f
'}]
commit_message:
Add end-of-file checks to bash8

Add two end-of-file checks to bash8.  Firstly, alert if heredoc hasn't
finished.  Some heredocs were done like:

---
sudo bash -c "cat <<EOF > foo
...
EOF"
---

(A better way to do this is "cat <<EOF | sudo tee ..." as it retains
the usual heredoc layout in the code).

The trailing quote was throwing the matching in bash8 off and it kept
appending the next file as if it was still part of the heredoc.  To
avoid this, we check if we're still in a heredoc when we start a new
file; if so raise an error and reset the heredoc status fresh.  We
track the state of the previous file, line and lineno so we can give a
good error.

---
E012: heredoc did not end before EOF: 'cat <<EOF'
 - lib/trove: L221
---

This includes fixes for the existing problem heredocs.

A similar EOF check is to ensure the previous file ended with a
newline.

---
E004: file did not end with a newline: '$MY_XTRACE'
 - lib/neutron_plugins/embrane: L40
---

This requires only one fix

Change-Id: I5e547d87b3921fc7ce6588c28f074e5c9f489c1f

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-02-23 22:35:45.000000000', 'files': ['functions-common', 'stackrc'], 'message': 'Add GIT_TIMEOUT variable to watch git operations

During my CI testing of each devstack change I can often see git get
itself stuck and hang indefinitely.  I'm not sure if it's transient
network issues, or issues at the remote end (seen with both github.com
and git.openstack.org) but it hits fairly frequently.  Retrying the
command usually gets it going again.  Searching for "git hanging" and
similar shows its not entirely uncommon...

This adds a watchdog timeout for remote git operations based on a new
environment variable GIT_TIMEOUT.  It will retry 3 times before giving

commit_message:
Add GIT_TIMEOUT variable to watch git operations

During my CI testing of each devstack change I can often see git get
itself stuck and hang indefinitely.  I'm not sure if it's transient
network issues, or issues at the remote end (seen with both github.com
and git.openstack.org) but it hits fairly frequently.  Retrying the
command usually gets it going again.  Searching for "git hanging" and
similar shows its not entirely uncommon...

This adds a watchdog timeout for remote git operations based on a new
environment variable GIT_TIMEOUT.  It will retry 3 times before giving
up.  The wrapper is applied to the main remote git calls.

Change-Id: I5b0114ca26b7ac2f25993264f761cba9ec8c09e1

commit_message:
Insecure check if keystone is up

If we start keystone with an SSL endpoint then the curl check to see if
it is running will fail because it cannot create a secure connection.
This check can be done insecurely as all we care about is that the
service has started.

Change-Id: I826753d4d46e9956f443110029346bc70282951a

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-02-26 11:43:20.000000000', 'files': ['spec/rabbitmq-server-redhat_spec.rb', 'recipes/rabbitmq-server.rb', 'spec/spec_helper.rb', 'attributes/default.rb', 'spec/rabbitmq-server_spec.rb'], 'message': "Install rabbitmq-server from rabbit site for CentOS/RHEL

Fixes: bug 1282041
Implements: blueprint centos-rhel-for-ops-messaging

On CentOS/RHEL, the OS base repos don't have a package for
rabbitmq-server.  The rabbitmq cookbook by default expects to be able to
install the latest rabbitmq-server rpm from the rabbitmq site
(use_distro_version = false).  However, in our cookbooks we are overriding
'use_distro_version' to true, which works for ubuntu as it has a
rabbitmq-server package in it's base repo

This commit basically leaves the use_distro_version flag as false unless
ubuntu/suse is the platform_family, so that CentOS/RHEL can grab the rpm
from the rabbitmq site

Change-Id: I4e31cbb4957f0e696a1528fa3f7c6c80695989ac
"}]
commit_message:
Install rabbitmq-server from rabbit site for CentOS/RHEL

Fixes: bug 1282041
Implements: blueprint centos-rhel-for-ops-messaging

On CentOS/RHEL, the OS base repos don't have a package for
rabbitmq-server.  The rabbitmq cookbook by default expects to be able to
install the latest rabbitmq-server rpm from the rabbitmq site
(use_distro_version = false).  However, in our cookbooks we are overriding
'use_distro_version' to true, which works for ubuntu as it has a
rabbitmq-server package in it's base repo

This commit basically leaves the use_distro_version flag as false unless
ubuntu/suse is the platform_family, so that CentOS/RHEL can grab the rpm
from the rabbitmq site

Change-Id: I4e31cbb4957f0e696a1528fa3f7c6c80695989ac

commit_message:
Refactor use of NotFound and ResourceExists exceptions

Removed all the {Objects}NotFound and {Objects}ResourceExists exceptions
and replaced their usage by raising directly NotFound and ResourceExists,
Added name and id parameter for NotFound and name for ResourceExists.

commit_message:
Fix the sample and unittest params of v3 scheduler-hints

The API samples of scheduler-hints contains "hypervisor" and "near"
attributes, but the attributes do not exist in the scheduler-hints
parameter of "create a server" API. This patch changes them to the
existing "same_host" attribute.
This patch also changes the attributes of some unit tests of the v3
scheduler-hints by the same attribute.

This nonexistent attributes are found during bp/nova-api-validation-fw
works. The implementation needs this change because it will deny the
unexpected attributes, which are not defined with API schema, in API
parameters.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1278279

Change-Id: I8542f44b325ba909fdff8b569146c0015b150291

subject: GlusterFS: Increase snapshot delete job timeout to two hours
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-26 17:21:07.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/glusterfs.py'], 'message': 'GlusterFS: Increase snapshot delete job timeout to two hours

Increase the timeout for Nova snapshot delete operations from ten
minutes to two hours.  This helps prevent Cinder from terminating
operations prematurely that are still being processed by Nova.

It is not uncommon for snapshot delete jobs to run for longer than
ten minutes depending on the size of the snapshot and speed of the
storage backend.

This will be followed up with a more robust mechanism to keep track

Related-Bug: 1273894

Change-Id: I1ad52568aed1ce1bf593e71704e481b6fe5f44fb
'}]
commit_message:
GlusterFS: Increase snapshot delete job timeout to two hours

Increase the timeout for Nova snapshot delete operations from ten
minutes to two hours.  This helps prevent Cinder from terminating
operations prematurely that are still being processed by Nova.

It is not uncommon for snapshot delete jobs to run for longer than
ten minutes depending on the size of the snapshot and speed of the
storage backend.

This will be followed up with a more robust mechanism to keep track
of snapshot job progress as a later effort.

Related-Bug: 1273894

Change-Id: I1ad52568aed1ce1bf593e71704e481b6fe5f44fb

subject: Fix fd leak from get_logger() in python 2.6
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2013-12-19 19:19:49.000000000', 'files': ['swift/common/utils.py', 'test/unit/common/test_utils.py'], 'message': 'Fix fd leak from get_logger() in python 2.6

Calling get_logger({}) instantiates a logging.handlers.SyslogHandler,
which opens and keeps a socket around (either /dev/log or UDP or
whatever; not important).

Under Python 2.6, all logging handlers instantiated anywhere at all
will live for the entire lifetime of the program; they get stored in
logging._handlerList and logging._handlers. Python 2.7 is very
similar, but uses weakrefs instead of strong references in those
module-level variables, so logging handlers can actually get cleaned
up prior to program exit.

The net effect is that any program that calls get_logger() more than a
fixed number of times will leak file descriptors under Python 2.6.

This commit throws encapsulation out the window and, under 2.6 only,
replaces strong references with weakrefs in logging._handlerList and
logging._handlers, thus avoiding the leak.

Change-Id: I5dc0d1619c5a4500f892b898afd9e3668ec0ee7c
'}]
commit_message:
Fix fd leak from get_logger() in python 2.6

Calling get_logger({}) instantiates a logging.handlers.SyslogHandler,
which opens and keeps a socket around (either /dev/log or UDP or
whatever; not important).

Under Python 2.6, all logging handlers instantiated anywhere at all
will live for the entire lifetime of the program; they get stored in
logging._handlerList and logging._handlers. Python 2.7 is very
similar, but uses weakrefs instead of strong references in those
module-level variables, so logging handlers can actually get cleaned
up prior to program exit.

The net effect is that any program that calls get_logger() more than a
fixed number of times will leak file descriptors under Python 2.6.

This commit throws encapsulation out the window and, under 2.6 only,
replaces strong references with weakrefs in logging._handlerList and
logging._handlers, thus avoiding the leak.

Change-Id: I5dc0d1619c5a4500f892b898afd9e3668ec0ee7c

commit_message:
Revert "Removed set_loaded() method from Resource class"

This patch broke python-novaclient.
It turns out novaclient uses get() to support lazy loading details.
Add a docstring to get() to clarify its usage.

see novaclient/tests/v3/test_servers.py#L54
This reverts commit 0c4d2c76a6876dd8873cca2736ca5a7f3da66c69.

Change-Id: I0a2936b00de3ca17f0e40e3d5226ecdaf1329295

commit_message:
Unbuffer log output

* Slow down exit paths: add sleep to die(), wait until last moment to
  kill child processes (including the awk log output filter)

There are two changes:
- Commit changes to the grant tables after each update to ensure MySQL
  doesn't get confused when there are multiple assignments for a given
  actor/target (Postgresql doesn't have this issue)
- Close any sessions in test_sql_upgarde before we call the migrations,
  to ensure table dropping won't be blocked

Fixes bug 1284700

Change-Id: I81704b17ea9c11be926018df125fcfdb79ee6271
"}]
commit_message:
Fix issue with DB upgrade to assignment table

There are two changes:
- Commit changes to the grant tables after each update to ensure MySQL
  doesn't get confused when there are multiple assignments for a given
  actor/target (Postgresql doesn't have this issue)
- Close any sessions in test_sql_upgarde before we call the migrations,
  to ensure table dropping won't be blocked

Fixes bug 1284700

Change-Id: I81704b17ea9c11be926018df125fcfdb79ee6271

commit_message:
BigSwitch: Fix tenant_id for shared net requests

The URI port requests are sent to on the backend
contains the tenant_id of the network. This corrects
a bug where, on port updates and deletes, the tenant_id
of the port rather than the network was being used,
which was incorrect when attached to a shared network.

Closes-Bug: #1278530
Change-Id: I09ffc767c669416555867e975d0b7057a5cfa0cb

commit_message:
notify calling process we are ready to serve

Systemd notification should be sent in-process, otherwise systemd might
miss the subprocess sending notification.
See systemd bug https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=820448

Taken from keystone project commit
abc06716d027d68f0da3b0f559fa7c85a21804d5

Improvements from Keystone version:

    * add unset_environment parameter
    New parameter unset_environment was added to sd_notify
    http://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/sd_notify.html
    to ensure service readiness is sent only once.

    * add onready() method to simulate systemd environment
    For testing purposes and optional use with SysV initscripts.

    * unit test added

    * docstrings for notification methods

Patch includes deployment in openstack.common.service.
It does not have an effect when running the service outside
the systemd environment.

Implements: blueprint service-readiness
Change-Id: I80f325c9be9c171c2dc8d5526570bf64f0f87c78

commit_message:
l2-population : send flooding entries when the last port goes down

Delete port used to call update_port_down to calculate
its fdb entries during delete_port_precommit. But during
the pre-commit, the port is still up, so update_port_down
acts as if there was still one port on the agent, and
doesn't add flooding entry in its fdb_entries.

Closes bug #1282141

Change-Id: Icedd02f33d999200505950beb9169ae3634e551b

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-10 11:44:42.000000000', 'files': ['nova/api/openstack/compute/contrib/scheduler_hints.py', 'nova/api/openstack/compute/plugins/v3/services.py', 'nova/api/openstack/compute/plugins/v3/scheduler_hints.py'], 'message': 'Replace detail for explanation msgs on webob exceptions.

When using detail=msg, a default msg is set and returned.
To let the user know the real cause of the error explanation arg
shall be set with the appropiate error message.

[For example]
$nova --os-compute-api-version 3 service-disable --reason 'A...' host srv
"The server could not comply with the request since it is either malformed
or otherwise incorrect."

By setting the explanation we get:
$nova --os-compute-api-version 3 service-disable --reason 'A...' host srv
ERROR: Disabled reason contains invalid characters or is too long

Change-Id: I380916b110cd021aefcbedd2f943155329860fe7
'}]
commit_message:
Replace detail for explanation msgs on webob exceptions.

When using detail=msg, a default msg is set and returned.
To let the user know the real cause of the error explanation arg
shall be set with the appropiate error message.

[For example]
$nova --os-compute-api-version 3 service-disable --reason 'A...' host srv
"The server could not comply with the request since it is either malformed
or otherwise incorrect."

By setting the explanation we get:
$nova --os-compute-api-version 3 service-disable --reason 'A...' host srv
ERROR: Disabled reason contains invalid characters or is too long

Change-Id: I380916b110cd021aefcbedd2f943155329860fe7

commit_message:
Empty email for users gets saved as an empty string

The actual behavior is that horizon sends an empty string
on the "email" field when creating a new user if the field
isn't filled by the user.
To match the keystone client behaviour, instead of sending
an empty string, this patch sends a "None" value when the
field isn't filled by the user.
By doing this, when creating a new user from both,
keystone client and horizon, a "null" value is stored
under the same conditions.
in the database. This will keep the data consistency.
From the presentation point of view, when a "null" value
is received, it is presented as an empty string instead
of showing "None" on the "email" field of the users table.

Change-Id: Ib5df774b3fe9d82c084f380c9c11aea46b2984aa
Closes-Bug: #1265805

commit_message:
Clean up _make_*_list in object models to use base.obj_make_list

There are a lot of places where _make_foo_list()s are implemented.
Actually base.obj_make_list() can be used to make the list.

The patch is to clean up the redundancies and make the code clean.

Also, in order to make _from_db_objects()s the same format, we add
'context' into the parameter list in instance fault object.

Related to blueprint icehouse-objects.

Change-Id: I1a68b6e9dc402d4e30a06f94b068233e2afa713f

commit_message:
Create V3 Auth Plugins

Extract the authentication code from a v3 client and move it to a series
of auth plugins. As v3 authentication can contain multiple
authentication methods this concept is represented by an AuthMethod. An
auth plugin then is provided with multiple mechanisms to authenticate
with.

There is also some helper class for the standard case where you only
need to authenticate with one method.

When a v3 client wants to do authentication it will create a new v3 auth
plugin, do the authentication and then take that result for the client
to use.

Change-Id: I5fa6a6e1c2e114e1428e35b723700c63a3cbed44
blueprint: auth-plugins

commit_message:
Create V2 Auth Plugins

Extract the authentication code from a v2 client and move it to a series
of auth plugins. Auth plugins each represent one method of
authenticating with a server and there is a factory method on the base
class to select the appropriate plugin from a group of arguments.

When a v2 client wants to do authentication it will create
a new v2 auth plugin, do the authentication and then take that result
for the client to use.

Change-Id: I4dd7474643ed5c2a3204ea2ec56029f926010c2c
blueprint: auth-plugins

[{'number': 9, 'created': '2014-02-24 13:45:28.000000000', 'files': ['tests/unit/scheduler/test_base_filter.py', 'openstack/common/scheduler/base_filter.py', 'openstack/common/scheduler/filters/availability_zone_filter.py'], 'message': "Allow filters to only run once per request if their data is static

Currently the filter_all() method of each scheduler filter is run
once for each resource in a request, but for many filters the data
doesn't change during a request.

commit_message:
Allow filters to only run once per request if their data is static

Currently the filter_all() method of each scheduler filter is run
once for each resource in a request, but for many filters the data
doesn't change during a request.

For example the data used by the AZ filter is pretty static, and
doesn't filter any more hosts on successive runs. However it is
fairly expensive to run on a large system.

Only filters that are based on data that may change within a
request, for example resource consumption, need to be evaluated
for each resource.

This patch adds a new attribute that allows filters to declare that
they only need to be run once per request. The default behavior is
left so that a filter is evaluated once for each resource in a
request.

Port from nova: Ia668f16414da86441323c58b1bbef5f88c81b90c

Change-Id: Ic656f1aa6830ed9b93c232a2098318e498a7d59e
Implements bp once-per-request-filters

Fix InstanceNotFound error in _delete_instance_files

commit_message:
Fix race condition when deleting a node

In the db api, between checking whether the node is not reserved and
deleting it from the db there was no lock, another request could acquire
that node and start an operation on it. This patch fixes it by locking
the node before it's deleted from the db.

This patch is also a plumbing because we might want to do operations
like changing the node's power state and stopping the console before
deleting a node.

Co-authored-by: Devananda van der Veen <devananda.vdv@gmail.com>

Change-Id: I5fd90f8321812f7636477c03a83038ad42d47817

commit_message:
Add zookeeper job/jobboard impl

Create a base implementation of a
jobboard which serves as a place to post
work to be done, a place to get notified of
new work, and a place which can be used to
atomically acquire that work (so that it
can be worked on) as well as transfer that
work from one entity (say when that entity
fails) to another entity (for further
resumption or other policy/code driven
recovery processes).

Implements: blueprint job-reference-impl

Change-Id: I1de1525df0deee612fb14ca36f0415ea7d2f707c

commit_message:
Wait for neutron ports to be ACTIVE before spawning instance

Previously, nova would spawn an instance before neutron was done wiring
an instance's ports. In this case the instance would come up but it's
networking would not be ready and the dhcp client in the instance would have
likely given up. This patch adds a method check_instance_network_active()
that is called in the compute/manager which polls neutron for the port
status and waits for the ports on an instance to go active before allowing
the instance to spawn.

DocImpact

commit_message:
Do not call trigger_instance_add/remove_security_group if quantum

If using quantum security groups in grizzly there is no need for the code to
call trigger_instance_remove_security_group_refresh,
trigger_instance_add_security_group_refresh as quantum handles all the
security groups. Calling these methods somethings causes the conductor to
timeout in large deployments.

Closes-bug: #1280021

Note: we don't need to merge this but I just put this patch up incase anyone
runs into this issue and wants this patch....

Change-Id: Ieb9aa0949fc999807422af36b9ca185cccb6cbcc

revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-02-18 18:04:15.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/libvirt/vif.py', 'nova/compute/manager.py'], 'message': "Set data in ovsdb even if libvirt version is >= 9011 and call plug_vifs

In libvirt version 9011 one does not need to explicitly call ovs-vsctl to
set external-ids:(iface-id, attached-mac, and vm-id) as long as it's included
in the the instance's xml file as libvirt will set this in ovsdb for you
automatically. Unfortinately, this doesn't propagate to ovsdb until the
instance is started. This patch restores the call to explicitly call ovs-vsctl
before the instance is launched so that neutron can start wiring the port.
This will allow us to poll neutron for the status of an instance's ports and
only start the instance when all of it's ports are ACTIVE.

Note: the plug_vifs and neutron status polling call will also need to be
added in a few additional places i.e: finish_migration,
finish_revert_migration, hard_reboot, and resume. Though this is just
a first step to optimize that the network is working when an instance

commit_message:
Set data in ovsdb even if libvirt version is >= 9011 and call plug_vifs

In libvirt version 9011 one does not need to explicitly call ovs-vsctl to
set external-ids:(iface-id, attached-mac, and vm-id) as long as it's included
in the the instance's xml file as libvirt will set this in ovsdb for you
automatically. Unfortinately, this doesn't propagate to ovsdb until the
instance is started. This patch restores the call to explicitly call ovs-vsctl
before the instance is launched so that neutron can start wiring the port.
This will allow us to poll neutron for the status of an instance's ports and
only start the instance when all of it's ports are ACTIVE.

Note: the plug_vifs and neutron status polling call will also need to be
added in a few additional places i.e: finish_migration,
finish_revert_migration, hard_reboot, and resume. Though this is just
a first step to optimize that the network is working when an instance
is spawned.

Related to blueprint: check-neutron-port-status

Change-Id: If05fb2d638e16d58cf8315a36d8cad87820663e6

subject: Remove tox locale overrides
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-10 03:02:43.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Remove tox locale overrides

* tox.ini: The LANG, LANGUAGE and LC_ALL environment overrides were
introduced originally during the testr migration in an attempt to be
conservative about the possibility that locale settings in the
calling environment could cause consistency problems for test runs.
In actuality, this should be unnecessary and any place where it does
cause issues ought to be considered an actual bug. Also, having
these in the configuration actively causes older pip to have
problems with non-ASCII content in some package metadata files under
Python 3, so drop it now.

Change-Id: I583ec3eb9ca50750b7b76c90822f1af7f3eb07a0
Closes-Bug: #1277495
'}]
commit_message:
Remove tox locale overrides

* tox.ini: The LANG, LANGUAGE and LC_ALL environment overrides were
introduced originally during the testr migration in an attempt to be
conservative about the possibility that locale settings in the
calling environment could cause consistency problems for test runs.
In actuality, this should be unnecessary and any place where it does
cause issues ought to be considered an actual bug. Also, having
these in the configuration actively causes older pip to have
problems with non-ASCII content in some package metadata files under
Python 3, so drop it now.

Change-Id: I583ec3eb9ca50750b7b76c90822f1af7f3eb07a0
Closes-Bug: #1277495

subject: BatchActions translate randomly to asian langs
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-20 20:06:40.000000000', 'files': ['horizon/tables/actions.py'], 'message': "BatchActions translate randomly to asian langs

BatchAction buttons are infrequently but most definitley being
translated into a random asian language.  This translation shouldn't be
happening, and is proving to be amazingly difficult to recreate in a
predictable way.

Currently, the best bet as to why this is happening is described here:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11883721/weird-django-translations-behaviour

The thing is, there's no need for the action or data_type objects to be
lazy at all, once inside the _get_action_name method.  So the solution
is to resolve them and then conjugate them within the pgettext_lazy
object.

Change-Id: I5f4ff8f713645194b8f00b9a73af56b79a4315fe
Closes-Bug: 1253982
"}]
commit_message:
BatchActions translate randomly to asian langs

BatchAction buttons are infrequently but most definitley being
translated into a random asian language.  This translation shouldn't be
happening, and is proving to be amazingly difficult to recreate in a
predictable way.

Currently, the best bet as to why this is happening is described here:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/11883721/weird-django-translations-behaviour

The thing is, there's no need for the action or data_type objects to be
lazy at all, once inside the _get_action_name method.  So the solution
is to resolve them and then conjugate them within the pgettext_lazy
object.

Change-Id: I5f4ff8f713645194b8f00b9a73af56b79a4315fe
Closes-Bug: 1253982

commit_message:
Shutdown the worker callback client

We are creating a new callback client for each job (in a long running
process), failing to close the connection to the server causes the
server to hold tcp connections open indefinitely and eventually hitting
its ulimit for open file descriptors.

Change-Id: Ic37a1f88d5c76a64752c06a59bb25bd004201071

commit_message:
Fix coverage option for run_tests.sh

This commit fixes run_tests.sh so that when the -c flag is specified
coverage will actually be collected. Previously the --coverage option
was added to testrargs, however this isn't a testr flag. It is used by
pbr to wrap testr with coverage start and coverage report. This changes
run_tests() so that when coverage is specified it runs the unit tests
using setup.py so that the coverage flag can be used.

Change-Id: Iad0d508b6a4638a67e45646148144f627588fa48

commit_message:
Scenario : Start instances using fixed network when possible

Uses the fixed_network_name option to select which network
to boot test instances on.  This allows Tempest to be run
in environments where there are multiple networks available.

Change-Id: I64ad6ce6bee3fe33537ac4f8d8d913856fe46554
Partial-Bug: #1250866

Move enablement of rhel6-optional repo earlier

Change 4f1fee6eae300a3384900df06ebc857e95854eb0 added the RHEL6
optional repo in fixup_stuff.sh, but it turns out that doesn't get run
until after the package prerequisites phase.  Move this into stack.sh
with the RDO repo setup.

commit_message:
Disable the NumericLiterals cop for rubocop

- Disable the NumericLiterals cop in the .rubocop.yml file - this cop enforces
  an underscore '_' every 3 characters of an integer. This doesn't make much
  sense in our use case and reduces readability. Especially for port numbers.

Change-Id: I32617941e3ee1f43e06fb5b9017e6ccab0cf5050
Addresses: blueprint rubocop-integer

  * check if the 'use_command' file exists:
  _ensure_rally_configuration_dir_exists(self)
  * update env var in the 'use_comand' file:

commit_message:
Refactor use deployment command

* Renamed 'deployment' filename in 'globals' in order to
use this file with other use subcommands such as 'task'
* Refactored by moving code into new generic functions that
  * check if the 'use_command' file exists:
  _ensure_rally_configuration_dir_exists(self)
  * update env var in the 'use_comand' file:
  _update_attribute_in_use_file(self, attribute, value)

Change-Id: I7734d34f99b468001bd431f98d97e4dade2236cd

commit_message:
NetApp fix create vol different size than snapshot

This fixes the issue of creating vol of different
size than snapshot and creating cloned vol of
different size than original.

This change adds a lot of additional LUN geometry
and sub-LUN cloning code which is neccesary to
support extreme resizes, since normal resize
operations are limitted to be within a certain factor
of the original LUN size.

Added the additional required methods in image_utils
and NetApp nfs driver that were added upstream.

Closes-Bug:#1098581

Conflicts:

	cinder/tests/test_netapp.py

commit_message:
Unify usage of storage error exception type

- Instead of formatting the exception by creating
  a storage error instance we can just let the already
  included cause make this formatting occur.
- Handle cases in impl_dir which were not catching and
  raising storage errors.
- Unify usage of 'backend internal error' messaging.
- Pass the cause to storage errors where applicable.

Change-Id: Ieb14256b202ccbfa3a96f68fa35db7e40f92114d

Change-Id: I5adb28c2d73c41792c1d67f51e11edfc7474ed99
